R1: None of these things are appropriate in this situation because the robot is so close to someone and the action is in the exact direction of that person, and it looks like people are standing around in a circle interacting in some way, so it would disrupt that social interaction.
R2: Any activities that are not noisy would be fine in the direction of the arrow, because it's away from the individuals who are interacting and would not disrupt them. Starting a conversation may be inappropriate because it would disrupt the social interaction in the room, since it's an open space. Mopping might be OK as it's quiet as long as no one from the group breaks away and walks in that direction not realising it's wet and slips. Vacuuming would likely be too noisy and might get in the way if someone from the group breaks away and wants to walk in that direction.
R3: I can't see an arrow, only a white circle, so assuming the actions are just within the circle space, vacuuming and mopping the floor would be fine, and perhaps starting a conversation, but the dog might disrupt other activities.
R4: Starting a conversation not appropriate as there are no other people around, though maybe it could talk to the dog and warn to stay away! Don't think the dog would disturb mopping or vacuuming so that would probably be OK. Would've thought there would be a risk with carrying food and drinks and small things with the dog there, unless the dog can be trained to obey the robot.
R5: All seems fine as no social interaction to disturb and not getting in anyone's way with any of these things.
R6: Too close to people to vacuum and hoover, and might get in the way of people. Carrying things should be OK but not big items as people are close by. Picking up things should be fine.
R7: Bit too close to person to mop or vacuum, and to carry large items, but carrying small things OK.
R8: Nobody around so no issues doing any of these activities.
R9: Vacuuming and mopping and moving large items not appropriate as could be a risk to person, and person may get in the way. Other activities fine.
R10: Mopping and vacuuming and carrying big items may get in the way and cause risk to person. Carrying small things should be fine, and saying hi or something else nice to other person would be appropriate.
R11: All seems reasonably OK as in other direction of dog, as long as it stops if dog comes near and poses a risk. Starting conversation with dog probably not appropriate unless giving it commands to stay away or saying something friendly so it isn't scared maybe!
R12: People around and v close so vacuuming and mopping not appropriate. Carrying things OK. Carrying big objects too close to other people so not appropriate. Could greet other people.
R13: Vacuuming or mopping in the circle might be OK as long as people know not to walk in that area. Carrying things seem OK as it's not disrupting others. Cleaning OK. People probably too close for large object carrying.
R14: Vacuuming or mopping in that circle would be where other people are walking so not appropriate. Carrying things OK as long as it can know to avoid people, walk between and around as humans would. Saying hi to others would be appropriate.
R15: As long as it can avoid other people or animals, would be ok to carry stuff around them. Mopping and vacuuming no good there because there is a dog and a person in the circle. R1: Given that the robot is surrounded by people, carrying large objects or hoovering is inappropriate, as the robot could bash into them and hurt them. Even if it would not do this, the people around might be scared. Everything else is very appropriate as it does not represent this danger

All the other activities would be very appropriate as they would not affect the humans and their activities.
R3: Carrying warm food around children could be dangerous: the food could get spilled on the child and burn them. Similarly, if the robot mopped here, the child or dog could slip and injure it/him/herself; and if carrying objects, the robot might drop them on the dog or child, or bump into them. Hoovering would frighten the dog. Anything else would be fine.

Picking up items would not get in the way of the humans, so is fine.

R1:
The scene depicts a social interaction with 5 people. We can assume that noisy actions, cleaning actions, carrying big objects or starting a conversation from the robot are inappropriate because too close from people. It would be a disturbance/interruption for the people who are interacting with each other.
Carrying food, drinks, small objects is appropriate but can still be a disturbance for the people interacting.
R2:
The robots is placed in a location more far from the people interacting. It is thus appropriate to carry food, drinks or small objects.
However, vacuuming and carrying big objects would be a disturbance for the people present. 
Mopping the floor is appropriate but could be done when people are not present in the room to avoid disturbance and potential accidents due to wet floor.
R3: Almost all actions are appropriate in this context. Some things could be done while people are not present (vacuum, mopping) and carrying big objects could harm the dog and the person that are close to the robot.
R4: Almost all actions are appropriate except the carrying of big objects as the robot is very close to the dog, and starting a conversation aiming at no one (not even the dog!) due to the direction of the arrow.
R5: Actions here are appropriate or inappropriate based on the fact that there are people in the room (so the robot should avoid vacuuming for example) but they are not close to the robot nor close to the direction it is taking (so the robot can carry things for example).
R6: All actions are inappropriate because the people are too close to the robot so any actions can be a disturbance or a potential danger.
R7: Most actions are appropriate except the ones that could be a disturbance for the person in the room/circle.
R8: All actions possible as no people nor animals are present in the room.
R9: All actions are inappropriate as a person is closely the robot. Actions should be done later or in a perimeter that is more far from the person.
R10: We can anticipate here that the person present in the room might take the stairs, thus crossing the arrow direction the robot is taking. So no action should be done by the robot, except to start a conversation as the person approaches.
R11: All actions can be done as the dog is far from the robot. Starting a conversation doesn't make sense here.
R12: It is a social context (many people, music playing, etc) so the robot could take actions that are related to hosting a party (food, drinks), but not cleaning actions or conversation at that time.
R13: All actions linked to hosting/taking care of the people present are appropriate. However, as there are people, actions such as cleaning or carrying big objects would be a disturbance no matter where the robot is in the room.
R14: There are several people but they are not interacting with each other. I would avoid any cleaning or carrying big objects from the robot in this context. Other actions are appropriate but have to be done carefully as people are around/in the circle.
R15: Appropriate actions related to hosting guests have to be done carefully as there is a person/dog in the circle. Cleaning and carrying big objects shouldn't be done as there are people/animal in the room interacting.
R16: Social interaction so the robot should avoid any disturbance (noise, carrying big objects, starting a conversation). Actions related to hosting the guests can be done but carefully, especially because a person is in the direction of the arrow.
R17: All actions are inappropriate as there are too many people close to the robot.
R18: People are in the room so the robot should avoid cleaning or carrying big objects. However, it is appropriate to carry food, drinks and small objects as the person closed to the robot is on their way.
R19:
People are in the room but not close to the robot and the direction it is taking, so all actions can be done overall.
Some actions could be done later when people are not present in the room anymore (noise, disturbance).
R20: Only carrying cold food, drinks and small objects are appropriate actions but have to be done carefully due to the presence of the child closely.
